  "text": "As expected, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] VitD and PTH inversely correlate (Fig. 2) . No effect of aging was observed on VitD (data not shown), whereas PTH increases along groups of age (R 2 ¼ 0.061, P < 0.001). The relationship between VitD and PTH, though, remains significant at each age group (20-40, 40-60 and 60-80 years, Fig. 2) . No effects of age on the relationship between VitD and PTH were observed in a multivariate analysis that included PTH as the dependent variable, and groups of age as a fixed factor and VitD as a covariate (VitD: F ¼ 35.931, P < 0.001; age groups: F ¼ 17.517, P < 0.001; VitD Â age groups: F ¼ 1.232, P ¼ 0.293).",
